Interface IWorkshop


  • public interface IWorkshop
    Service for running jobs concurrently.
    Since:
    1.1
    See Also:
    IRunnable, IWorkshopProfiler

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void run(IRunnable job, IArgList argList)

    • Method Detail

      • run

        void run(Runnable job)
        Assigns the given job to a worker thread to run at some time in the future.
        Parameters:
        job - the runnable task
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given job is null
        RejectedExecutionException - if the workshop is shutdown or the current thread is interrupted

      • run

        void run(IRunnable job,
       IArgList argList)
        Assigns the given job to a worker thread to run at some time in the future. The given argList will be passed to job.run.
        Parameters:
        job - the runnable task
        argList - the arguments to be passed to job.run
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given job is null
        RejectedExecutionException - if the workshop is shutdown or the current thread is interrupted
